**[1857, 08-11] Ms.B.1.6.6.58**

May Jr. to RDW

Discusses Hinton Helper’s *Impending Crisis* at length. Says the book
shows that “the seeds, which the Antislavery Agitation has scattered,
have not all perished or been cast on rocky and barren soil; but that
some have germinated, and are about to yield fruit manifold.”


